NAME
MISC_inet_nultoa - return string representation of "dotted" IP address

SYNOPSIS
#include <misc.h>
char *MISC_inet_nultoa(unsigned long inaddr) ;

DESCRIPTION
Provided a network byte-ordered unsigned long Internet address,
MISC_inet_nultoa returns a pointer to the string representation
of the "dotted" IP address.

"nultoa" corresponds to "Network Unsigned Long TO ASCII".

RETURN VALUE
Pointer to string representation of "dotted" IP address.  This string
will be "000.000.000.000" if the conversion fails for any reason.

NOTES
Network byte-order is assumed to be Big Endian.

This routine replaces inet_ntoa(), which does not conform to any
known standard.
